  "body": "I was looking at the `Tabular` class (in shap/shap/maskers/_tabular.py) and saw that the input data is sampled using the `utils.sample` function (defined in shap/shap/utils/_general.py).\r\n\r\nThis function samples a dataset using `sklearn.utils.resample(X, n_samples=nsamples, random_state=random_state)`. The default behavior of the sklearn's function is to implement resampling **with replacement**.\r\nIs this wanted here ?\r\n\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport pandas as pd\r\nimport numpy as np\r\nfrom shap.utils._general import sample\r\n\r\n# Fake data\r\ndf = pd.DataFrame({'x': [i for i in range(100)], 'y': [i / 10 for i in range(100)]})\r\n\r\n# Sample 99 data (will use replacement)\r\nsampled_data_99 = sample(df.values, 99)\r\nlen(np.unique(sampled_data_99 , axis=0))  # -> 62\r\n\r\n# Sample 100 data (will take all the dataset)\r\nsampled_data_100 = sample(df.values, 100)\r\nlen(np.unique(sampled_data_100 , axis=0))  # -> 100\r\n```\r\n",
